views.text: The bagworm is, in fact, not a worm at all, but a caterpillar instead. The filthy fraud uses silk and leaves to spin a cozy bag for it to hide inside—hence the name. Some find it cute the way bagworms dangle from trees. But the truth is they're gluttonous monsters. These beasts love to stuff their bug- gullets full of leaves, devouring the very trees they hang upon. Wretched villains is what they are.
I caught a bagworm! Guess I'm a bragworm!
